resources.name: x86-ubuntu-18.04-boot
resources.documentation: A full boot of Ubuntu 18.04 with Linux 5.4.49 for X86. It runs an `m5 exit` command when the boot is completed unless the readfile is specified. If specified the readfile will be executed after booting.

resources.name: riscv-ubuntu-20.04-boot
resources.documentation: A full boot of Ubuntu 20.04 with Linux 5.10 for RISCV. It runs an `m5 exit` command when the boot is completed unless the readfile is specified. If specified the readfile will be executed after booting.

resources.name: arm64-ubuntu-20.04-boot
resources.documentation: A full boot of Ubuntu 20.04 with Linux 5.4.49 for ARM64. It runs an `m5 exit` command when the boot is completed unless the readfile is specified. If specified the readfile will be executed after booting.

resources.name: x86-print-this-15000-with-simpoints
resources.documentation: This workload is used in the 'configs/example/gem5_library/checkpoints/simpoints-se-checkpoint.py' example configuration script.

resources.name: x86-print-this-15000-with-simpoints-and-checkpoint
resources.documentation: This workload is used in the 'configs/example/gem5_library/checkpoints/simpoints-se-restore.py' example configuration script.

resources.name: x86-print-this-1500-simpoints
resources.documentation: Simpoints for running the 'x86-print-this' resource with the parameters `"print this" 15000`. This is encapsulated in the 'x86-print-this-15000-with-simpoints' workload.

resources.name: vega-mmio
resources.documentation: Used with the 'x86-gpu-fs-img' disk image.

resources.name: riscv-hello-example-checkpoint

resources.name: simpoints-se-checkpoints-v22-1

resources.name: riscv-hello-example-checkpoint-v22-1

resources.name: x86-m5-exit
